headline: Are Wall Street Analysts Bullish on Erie Indemnity Stock?
summary: While Erie Indemnity has lagged behind the broader market over the past year, analysts are cautiously bullish on its future potential.

headline: ERIE Q2 Deep Dive: Cybersecurity Incident and Catastrophe Losses Shape Results
summary: Insurance management company Erie Indemnity (NASDAQ:ERIE) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales rose 7% year on year to $1.06 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.35 per share was 5.7% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
